
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "EuropeDestinations";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

@section Styles {
    <link href="~/Content/popular_destinations.css" rel="stylesheet" />
}

<div class="region-section">
    <div class="region-header">
        <h2>Europe</h2>
        <p>Rich history, stunning architecture, and diverse cultures</p>
    </div>

    <div class="destination-blog">

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/The-Eiffel-Tower-Frances-Global-Icon.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Paris, France</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Eiffel Tower</h3>
                <p>The iconic iron lattice tower stands 330 meters tall and offers breathtaking views of Paris. Visit at sunset for an unforgettable experience as the city lights up below you.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/colosseum.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Rome, Italy</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Colosseum</h3>
                <p>This ancient amphitheater is a testament to Roman engineering and gladiatorial history. Walk through 2,000 years of history in one of the world's most recognizable monuments.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Engelsburg_und_Engelsbrücke_abends.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Rome, Italy</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Castel Sant’Angelo</h3>
                <p>Castel Sant’Angelo is a historic fortress in Rome originally built as Emperor Hadrian’s mausoleum. Over the centuries, it served as a castle, papal refuge, and military stronghold. Today, it stands as one of Rome’s most iconic landmarks overlooking the Tiber River.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/sagrada.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Barcelona, Spain</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Sagrada Familia</h3>
                <p>Gaudí's masterpiece has been under construction since 1882. The stunning basilica combines Gothic and Art Nouveau forms, creating one of the most unique churches in the world.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Catedral\ de\ Sevilla\,\ Seville.jpg ');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Seville, Spain</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Seville Cathedral</h3>
                <p>The world’s largest Gothic cathedral, famous for its soaring arches, intricate details, and the historic Giralda Tower, this monumental structure stands as a testament to centuries of craftsmanship and remains one of Spain’s most awe-inspiring architectural achievements.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Hofburg\ Palace\,\ Vienna.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Vienna, Austria</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Hofburg Palace</h3>
                <p>This imperial palace served as the home of the Habsburg dynasty for centuries and is one of Vienna’s most iconic architectural landmarks.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/hohensalzburg_fortress_plTt5yy.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Salzburg, Austria</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Hohensalzburg Fortress</h3>
                <p>One of Europe’s largest medieval fortresses, offering panoramic views of Salzburg and well-preserved historic architecture, this imposing stronghold stands as a remarkable symbol of the city’s heritage and provides visitors with a vivid glimpse into centuries of fortress life and defensive ingenuity.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Brandenburg\ Gate\,\ Berlin.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Berlin, Germany</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Brandenburg Gate</h3>
                <p>This neoclassical monument is one of Berlin’s most famous landmarks and a historic symbol of peace and unity, standing at the heart of the city as a reminder of Germany’s cultural resilience and its journey toward reunification.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/catedrall.png');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Cologne,Germany</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Cologne Cathedral</h3>
                <p>This towering Gothic cathedral features twin spires and stunning stained-glass windows, making it one of Germany’s most iconic churches and a masterpiece of medieval architecture that dominates the Cologne skyline and draws millions of visitors each year.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/oia_santorini_sunset.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Santorini, Germany</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Santorini</h3>
                <p>Famous for its white-washed houses and stunning sunsets, Santorini offers breathtaking views over the caldera, crystal-blue waters, and a uniquely romantic atmosphere, creating an unforgettable blend of natural beauty and island charm that captivates visitors from around the world..</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/disney-castle-neuschwanstein.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Schwangau, Germany</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Neuschwanstein Castle</h3>
                <p>Neuschwanstein Castle is a fairytale palace built by King Ludwig II in the Bavarian Alps. Its dramatic cliffs, towers, and stunning mountain backdrop make it one of Germany’s most iconic landmarks. The castle’s romantic design even inspired Disney’s Sleeping Beauty castle.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/big-ben.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 London, UK</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Big Ben & Houses of Parliament</h3>
                <p>The iconic clock tower has been keeping time over London since 1859. The Gothic architecture of the Houses of Parliament creates a stunning backdrop along the River Thames.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


    </div>
</div>

</div>

